.TH "drbd_md_read" 9 "drbd_md_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drbd_md_read \- Reads in the meta data super block
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drbd_md_read
.BI "(struct drbd_device *device "  ","
.BI "struct drbd_backing_dev *bdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
DRBD device.
.IP "bdev" 12
Device from which the meta data should be read in.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return NO_ERROR on success, and an enum drbd_ret_code in case
something goes wrong.

Called exactly once during \fBdrbd_adm_attach\fP, while still being D_DISKLESS,
even before \fIbdev\fP is assigned to \fIdevice->ldev\fP.
